1)ViewControllerRegistry:ViewControllerRegistry allows to create simple automated controllers pre-configured with status 
code and/or a view.
@Configuration
public class AppConfig implements WebMvcConfigurer {

    @Override
    public void addViewControllers(ViewControllerRegistry registry) {
        registry.addViewController("/hello").setViewName("hello");
    }
}

2)@Configuration: annotation which indicates that the class has @Bean definition methods. 
3)@Bean:@Bean annotation which is applied on a method to specify that it returns a bean to be managed by Spring context